  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: 'In order to kill an enemy you have to get in range by moving close to
    them and then hitting them with an attack. Moving, attacking and defending cost
    ENERGY, for you and for the enemies.


    Each tile of movement costs 2 energy.
    When attacked you will exhaust as much energy as needed to mitigate attack damage.
    Unmitigated damage is suffered as final damage which adds to the score.  When
    attacking, you can choose the amount of energy to spend from none to all.


    Enemies
    have a predicateble way of using energy and doing actions, use your premonitious
    skills to defeat them with as little effort possible.


    There are two types
    of enemy skeletons: archers and swordsmen. They act differently.


    Utilize
    highpoints which will give better damage resistance and higher damage output.'
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
